diffr 0.9.0
------------------------------------------------------------------------------
* Deploying package for Bioconductor submission, i.e. fixing errors and warnings
  in R CMD check and R CMD BiocCheck

diffr 0.7.0
------------------------------------------------------------------------------
* Standardized enrichment computation in C++
  - enrichment can be well compared between various ChIP-seq experiments
* exportR() function provides methods to export results of fits as a region bed
   file or bigWig track of standardized enrichment

* Finishing up tests.

diffr 0.4.0
------------------------------------------------------------------------------
* Performance:
  - huge performance speedup by reducing needed operations to unique tupels only
  - mapToUniquePairs() saves double computation for same (r,s)-tupels (~10%
    unique pairs needed for computation only)
  - OpenMP parallelization of matrix log row sum computation with user
     specified number of kernels
  - Kahan summation for log posterior summation to reduce numerical error
* Functionality:
  - fixed tilde bug for bampaths
  - removed diffcall(): diffR() will do both enrichment and difference calling
    in the future
  - src/Makevars added for OpenMP compatibility
* Documentation:
  - updated to restructuring

diffr 0.3.1
------------------------------------------------------------------------------
* Pvalue computation done in logspace in C++

diffr 0.3.0
------------------------------------------------------------------------------
* Performance:
  - processByChromosome is now generic for length(bam.files) > 2
  - P-value computation and adjustment done in R wrappers
* Functionality:
  - em.cpp::em() returns q* = #ChIP-tags/(#Input-tags + #ChIP-tags)
  - wrappers take counts directly or path to bam file with index

diffr 0.1.0
------------------------------------------------------------------------------
* diffr packaging started with migrating difference calling pipeline scripts
  and C++ code to this packages
* roxygen2 documentation
* ./tests/testthat created
* ./exec/ holds commandline scripts
